rComments: Professor Dinovitzer was one of the best sociology professors I've had thus far. She really knows how to keep you engaged. However, the grading scheme is crazy; 2 essays @ 37.5% each and a final test at 25%. Essay prompts were easy but the TA's expected a lot considering that we would loose grades if we went over the word count. Enjoyable class!!

Very engaging lectures. There is no textbook but she links the readings and they are necessary for the essays, but they are for the most part interesting. the course is heavily weighted on the essays so if that scares you I could not recommend it, but overall one of my favourite courses have taken and one of my favourite professors.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Her TAs are such hard graders,  they don't give clear criteria prior to the assignment being due  the Prof is pretty good, she's clear and engaged in her lectures, however, she doesnt give breaks, but ends about 10 minutes early

rComments: great prof overall, but gotta do the readings. it is 4th year afterall
love her! She made the class so engaging, even though i didn't want to be a lawyer. This was my highest mark EVER! Her tests are really fair! Too bad I didn't take more of her courses!

Took Sociology of Law and a seminar with her. Excellent prof. always looking for hr students to do their best. Easy to talk to, fair tests and assignments, explains everything clearly and with great examples. She tries to make her lectures very interesting and I'd say she's doing a good job at it. LOVE HER. Wish more prof's were like her.
Great prof...she's new and loves what she's doing, interesting lectures. Fair tests and assignments. Overall great prof and very easy to approach and talk to =)
